  "issue_title": "feature: add clear_text tool",
  "issue_body": "Parent: #75\n\n## Problem\n\nTouchPilot can type text, but it does not have a reliable primitive for clearing or replacing existing field content.\n\nThis blocks common workflows such as editing search terms, replacing settings values, or retrying failed form entry.\n\n## Proposed behavior\n\nAdd a `clear_text` Android tool that clears the focused or resolved input field.\n\nExpected behavior:\n\n- use a resolved input target when selector args are provided,\n- otherwise operate on the currently focused editable field,\n- return a clear failure when no editable target is available,\n- avoid logging existing field contents.\n\n## User workflow\n\nA user can ask TouchPilot to clear a field before typing a new value.\n\n## Local-first impact\n\nReliable local form control needs clear/replace behavior before Milestone 5 multi-step tasks.\n\n## Safety and security considerations\n\nClearing text can delete user-entered data. The tool should use the normal policy/risk path and must not log previous field contents.\n\n## Acceptance criteria\n\n- [ ] Add `clear_text` to the Android tool catalog.\n- [ ] Support focused-field and resolved-target modes.\n- [ ] Return actionable errors for no editable target or ambiguous target.\n- [ ] Do not log raw field contents.\n- [ ] Add unit tests and live-test checklist coverage.\n\n## Alternatives considered\n\nUse repeated delete key events through a generic key tool. Rejected for now because a focused clear primitive is easier to verify and constrain.\n",
  "merged_at": "2026-05-27T16:52:55.000Z",
